Package de.rwth.i2.attestor

All classes related to the attestor project.

See: Description

Package de.rwth.i2.attestor Description

All classes related to the attestor project. In particular, this includes the following packages:

  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.main containsSubsumingState the main Attestor class that is used to customize and execute an analysis. It also containsSubsumingState the general interface for all analysis programState. The actual execution of the full tool as well as integration test should always create an Attestor object that is fed with command line options and/or setting files. All global options are handled in the subpackage de.rwth.i2.attestor.phases.communication.
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.stateSpaceGeneration containsSubsumingState the data structures and algorithms to generate a state space. The state space generation itself is configurable through various programState.
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.graph containsSubsumingState the all algorithms and data structures on hypergraphs. In particular, heap configurations, i.e. our representation of program memory, are implemented in de.rwth.i2.attestor.graph.heap. Furthermore, algorithms to check for embeddings and isomorphism of two graphs are implemented in de.rwth.i2.attestor.graph.morphism. representation
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.semantics containsSubsumingState all implementations of the abstract program semantics (implementation of SemanticsCommand).
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.grammar containsSubsumingState an implementation of hyperedge replacement grammars and grammar transformations.
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.io containsSubsumingState all classes to load and export heap configurations, grammars, and state spaces.
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.types defines the general type of nodes (classes) to be analyzed.
  • de.rwth.i2.attestor.util containsSubsumingState small auxiliary classes that fit nowhere else.
Author:
Christoph
